        <summary type="html"><![CDATA[ritical vulnerability has been identified in the React Server Components in Next.js]]></summary>
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p><strong>Published:</strong> December 3rd, 2025<br>
<strong>CVSS Score:</strong> 10.0 (Critical)<br>
<strong>Source:</strong> <a href="https://nextjs.org/blog/CVE-2025-66478" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Next.js Security Advisory</a></p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="overview">Overview<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#overview" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Overview" title="Direct link to Overview" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>A critical vulnerability has been identified in the React Server Components (RSC) protocol that can allow remote code execution (RCE) when processing attacker-controlled requests in unpatched environments. This vulnerability originates from the upstream React implementation (<a href="https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2025-55182" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">CVE-2025-55182</a>).</p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="impact">Impact<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#impact" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Impact" title="Direct link to Impact" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>The vulnerable RSC protocol allowed untrusted inputs to influence server-side execution behavior. Under specific conditions, an attacker could craft requests that trigger unintended server execution paths, resulting in remote code execution.</p>
<p><strong>All users should upgrade to a patched version immediately.</strong></p>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="affected-versions">Affected Versions<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#affected-versions" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Affected Versions" title="Direct link to Affected Versions" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>Applications using React Server Components with the App Router are affected when running:</p>
<ul>
<li>Next.js 15.x</li>
<li>Next.js 16.x</li>
<li>Next.js 14.3.0-canary.77 and later canary releases</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Not affected:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Next.js 13.x</li>
<li>Next.js 14.x stable</li>
<li>Pages Router applications</li>
<li>Edge Runtime</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="fixed-versions">Fixed Versions<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#fixed-versions" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Fixed Versions" title="Direct link to Fixed Versions" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<p>The vulnerability is fully resolved in:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>15.0.5</strong> (for 15.0.x)</li>
<li><strong>15.1.9</strong> (for 15.1.x)</li>
<li><strong>15.2.6</strong> (for 15.2.x)</li>
<li><strong>15.3.6</strong> (for 15.3.x)</li>
<li><strong>15.4.8</strong> (for 15.4.x)</li>
<li><strong>15.5.7</strong> (for 15.5.x)</li>
<li><strong>16.0.7</strong> (for 16.0.x)</li>
<li><strong>15.6.0-canary.58</strong> (for 15.x canary releases)</li>
<li><strong>16.1.0-canary.12</strong> (for 16.x canary releases)</li>
</ul>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="solution-how-to-fix-the-vulnerability">Solution: How to Fix the Vulnerability<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#solution-how-to-fix-the-vulnerability" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Solution: How to Fix the Vulnerability" title="Direct link to Solution: How to Fix the Vulnerability" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-1-check-your-current-version">Step 1: Check Your Current Version<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-1-check-your-current-version" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 1: Check Your Current Version" title="Direct link to Step 1: Check Your Current Version" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>First, verify which version of Next.js you're currently using:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm list next</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># or</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">cat package.json | grep next</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-2-choose-your-upgrade-path">Step 2: Choose Your Upgrade Path<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-2-choose-your-upgrade-path" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 2: Choose Your Upgrade Path" title="Direct link to Step 2: Choose Your Upgrade Path" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<h4 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="option-a-automated-fix-tool-recommended">Option A: Automated Fix Tool (Recommended)<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#option-a-automated-fix-tool-recommended" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Option A: Automated Fix Tool (Recommended)" title="Direct link to Option A: Automated Fix Tool (Recommended)" translate="no">â€‹</a></h4>
<p>The easiest way to fix the vulnerability is using the official automated tool:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npx fix-react2shell-next</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>This interactive tool will:</p>
<ul>
<li>Check your current Next.js version</li>
<li>Determine the correct patched version for your release line</li>
<li>Automatically update your <code>package.json</code> and <code>package-lock.json</code></li>
<li>Provide clear instructions for next steps</li>
</ul>
<h4 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="option-b-manual-upgrade">Option B: Manual Upgrade<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#option-b-manual-upgrade" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Option B: Manual Upgrade" title="Direct link to Option B: Manual Upgrade" translate="no">â€‹</a></h4>
<p>If you prefer to upgrade manually, install the appropriate patched version based on your current release:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># For Next.js 15.0.x</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@15.0.5</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># For Next.js 15.1.x</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@15.1.9</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># For Next.js 15.2.x</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@15.2.6</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># For Next.js 15.3.x</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@15.3.6</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># For Next.js 15.4.x</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@15.4.8</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># For Next.js 15.5.x</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@15.5.7</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># For Next.js 16.0.x</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@16.0.7</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h4 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="option-c-upgrade-to-latest-stable-recommended-for-new-projects">Option C: Upgrade to Latest Stable (Recommended for New Projects)<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#option-c-upgrade-to-latest-stable-recommended-for-new-projects" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Option C: Upgrade to Latest Stable (Recommended for New Projects)" title="Direct link to Option C: Upgrade to Latest Stable (Recommended for New Projects)" translate="no">â€‹</a></h4>
<p>If you're starting fresh or can upgrade to the latest version:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@latest</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>This will install the latest patched version (16.0.7 or newer).</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-3-handle-canary-releases">Step 3: Handle Canary Releases<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-3-handle-canary-releases" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 3: Handle Canary Releases" title="Direct link to Step 3: Handle Canary Releases" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>If you're using canary releases:</p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Next.js 14.3.0-canary.77 or later:</strong> Downgrade to stable 14.x</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@14</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Using canary for PPR (Partial Prerendering):</strong> Update to a patched canary</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@15.6.0-canary.58   # for 15.x canary</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install next@16.1.0-canary.12   # for 16.x canary</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-4-update-dependencies">Step 4: Update Dependencies<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-4-update-dependencies" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 4: Update Dependencies" title="Direct link to Step 4: Update Dependencies" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>After installing the patched version, update your lock file:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># or</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm update</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-5-verify-the-fix">Step 5: Verify the Fix<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-5-verify-the-fix" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 5: Verify the Fix" title="Direct link to Step 5: Verify the Fix" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>Confirm that the patched version is installed:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm list next</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>You should see one of the patched versions listed in the "Fixed Versions" section above.</p>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-6-test-your-application">Step 6: Test Your Application<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-6-test-your-application" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 6: Test Your Application" title="Direct link to Step 6: Test Your Application" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>Before deploying, thoroughly test your application:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm run build</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm run start</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<p>Test critical functionality, especially:</p>
<ul>
<li>Server Components</li>
<li>API routes</li>
<li>Server Actions</li>
<li>Data fetching</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-7-deploy-the-patched-version">Step 7: Deploy the Patched Version<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-7-deploy-the-patched-version" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 7: Deploy the Patched Version" title="Direct link to Step 7: Deploy the Patched Version" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>Deploy your updated application to production immediately:</p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># Example for Vercel</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">vercel --prod</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain" style="display:inline-block"></span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain"># Example for other platforms</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">git add package.json package-lock.json</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">git commit -m "security: upgrade Next.js to patch CVE-2025-66478"</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">git push</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-8-rotate-secrets-critical">Step 8: Rotate Secrets (Critical)<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-8-rotate-secrets-critical" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 8: Rotate Secrets (Critical)" title="Direct link to Step 8: Rotate Secrets (Critical)" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p><strong>If your application was online and unpatched as of December 4th, 2025 at 1:00 PM PT</strong>, you must rotate all secrets:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Environment Variables:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Database credentials</li>
<li>API keys</li>
<li>OAuth secrets</li>
<li>JWT secrets</li>
<li>Encryption keys</li>
<li>Any other sensitive credentials</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>How to Rotate:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Update values in your hosting platform (Vercel, AWS, etc.)</li>
<li>Update <code>.env</code> files (never commit these!)</li>
<li>Update CI/CD pipeline secrets</li>
<li>Update third-party service API keys</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Priority Order:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Start with most critical secrets (database, payment processors)</li>
<li>Then rotate API keys and OAuth credentials</li>
<li>Finally, rotate less critical keys</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="step-9-monitor-for-issues">Step 9: Monitor for Issues<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#step-9-monitor-for-issues" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Step 9: Monitor for Issues" title="Direct link to Step 9: Monitor for Issues" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>After deployment:</p>
<ul>
<li>Monitor application logs for errors</li>
<li>Check error tracking (Sentry, etc.)</li>
<li>Verify all features work correctly</li>
<li>Monitor for any suspicious activity</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="important-notes">Important Notes<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#important-notes" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Important Notes" title="Direct link to Important Notes" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>No Workaround Available:</strong> There is no workaround for this vulnerability. Upgrading is the only solution.</li>
<li><strong>Immediate Action Required:</strong> This is a critical RCE vulnerability. Upgrade as soon as possible.</li>
<li><strong>Backward Compatibility:</strong> Patched versions maintain backward compatibility with your existing code.</li>
<li><strong>Breaking Changes:</strong> The security patches do not introduce breaking changes to the Next.js API.</li>
</ul>
<h3 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="troubleshooting">Troubleshooting<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#troubleshooting" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Troubleshooting" title="Direct link to Troubleshooting" translate="no">â€‹</a></h3>
<p>If you encounter issues during upgrade:</p>
<ol>
<li>
<p><strong>Clear cache:</strong></p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">rm -rf .next</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">rm -rf node_modules</span><br></span><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm install</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Check for conflicting dependencies:</strong></p>
<div class="language-bash codeBlockContainer_Ckt0 theme-code-block" style="--prism-color:#F8F8F2;--prism-background-color:#282A36"><div class="codeBlockContent_QJqH"><pre tabindex="0" class="prism-code language-bash codeBlock_bY9V thin-scrollbar" style="color:#F8F8F2;background-color:#282A36"><code class="codeBlockLines_e6Vv"><span class="token-line" style="color:#F8F8F2"><span class="token plain">npm ls react react-dom</span><br></span></code></pre></div></div>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Review Next.js migration guide:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/upgrading/version-15" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Next.js 15 Upgrade Guide</a></li>
<li><a href="https://nextjs.org/docs/app/building-your-application/upgrading/version-16" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Next.js 16 Upgrade Guide</a></li>
</ul>
</li>
</ol>
<h2 class="anchor anchorWithStickyNavbar_LWe7" id="resources">Resources<a href="https://shiguredd.github.io/blog/nextjs-rsc-cve#resources" class="hash-link" aria-label="Direct link to Resources" title="Direct link to Resources" translate="no">â€‹</a></h2>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://github.com/vercel/next.js/security/advisories/GHSA-9qr9-h5gf-34mp" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Next.js Security Advisory (CVE-2025-66478)</a></li>
<li><a href="https://www.cve.org/CVERecord?id=CVE-2025-55182" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">React Security Advisory (CVE-2025-55182)</a></li>
<li><a href="https://react.dev/blog/2025/12/03/critical-security-vulnerability-in-react-server-components" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">React Blog: Critical Security Vulnerability</a></li>
